{"title":"Kona Ouroboros Adds Aluminum Frame, Expanding Adventure Gravel Bike Family","link":"https://bikerumor.com/kona-ouroboros-adds-aluminum-frame-expanding-adventure-gravel-bike-family/","date":1747930967000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL_composite-1536x1024.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros adventure gravel bike\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://konaworld.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kona Bicycles</a>‘ Ouroboros line of drop-bar adventure bikes is a good-looking bunch. With long chainstays, slack headtube angles, and plenty of mounting points, they are unique and purpose-built. Many iterations, specs, and frame materials are available. And now, you can get one in a more affordable aluminum frame, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Kona Ouroboros AL affordable 6061 aluminum adventure</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros fist pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-fist-pic-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption><em>(Photos / Kona)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kona Ouroboros is a bike that is said to be “impressively capable”. It’s decked out with no-nonsense componentry that is reliable and delivers consistent performance. Kona says the whole Ouroboros is specifically designed to escape into the wilderness and stay off the grid, and this new aluminum version makes that more affordable than ever!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros back side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-back-side-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Kona Says About the Ouroboros</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Kona combined “<em>the best parts of their award-winning gravel bikes, and the enchanting characteristics of their iconic mountain bikes, and delivered a drop bar bike that doesn’t rip by accident</em>.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>The Ouroboros is a construct – a shapeshifter, if you will. We’ve offered you four forms, but maybe you need more. Maybe you need less. Maybe it’s time we step aside and let you work your own magic. Choose from a carbon frameset or an aluminum one, both equipped with an Ouroboros carbon fork. Dream up the ultimate build for the deepest corners of the world—and conjure it into reality”.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros front tri\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-tri-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros front end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-front-end-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ouroboros AL Tech Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-cockpit-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>butted 6061 aluminum alloy frame</li>\n\n\n\n<li>UDH – T-type compatible</li>\n\n\n\n<li>conventional internal cable routing through modular downtube routing ports</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1.5″ tapered headset </li>\n\n\n\n<li>round 31.9mm seatpost (34.9mm seatclamp) with internal dropper post routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>PF86 bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>1x, 2x, and even 3x compatible (band clamp bottom pull front derailleur compatible)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flat mount 160mm brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>12mm x 100/142mm thru-axles</li>\n\n\n\n<li>max 53mm (29×2.1″) tire clearance</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6 frame sizes available (48-58cm)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork.webp\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork.webp\" alt=\"Kona Ouroboros AL affordable 6061 aluminum adventure bike geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork.webp 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork-297x178.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork-1536x922.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork-120x72.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Kona-Ouroboros-AL-geometry-with-suspension-fork-768x461.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Kona Ouoboros Spec Highlights</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros mounts for days\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-mounts-for-days-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros down tube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-down-tube-logo-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Suntour GVX 32</strong> – 40mm travel gravel suspension fork with direct flat mount brake, 12x100mm thru-axle, adjustable rebound damping, and a lockout.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Maxxis Ravager TL EXO 700x50mm</strong> – Fast-rolling tubeless tires, but still aggressive enough to grab the corners.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>125mm travel TransX Dropper Post, 125mm w/ integrated lever</strong> – A 31.6 diameter dropper with dedicated left brake lever-integrated remote keeps your hand on the bars. The diameter means a beefy, durable dropper, and a common size to easily source a replacement at the end of its service life.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Microshift 11-48t 10-speed drivetrain</strong> – Big range cassette on a classic Shimano HG freehub, with excellent gear gaps to keep things simple and offer consistent shifting.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Kona Ouoboros Aluminum – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"750\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros frameset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256-297x174.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256-120x70.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-frameset-e1747870182256-768x450.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new aluminum Ouoboros is now available to order from your local Kona dealer, either as a complete bike or a separate frameset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A frameset alone will run you $1150, combining the new 6061 alloy frame with the full carbon Ouoboros adventure fork (up to 2.5″ tire clearance!) </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"777\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160.webp\" alt=\"New Aluminum Kona Ouroboros hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160-297x180.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160-120x73.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/New-Aluminum-Kona-Ouroboros-hero-e1747870098160-768x466.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Just one complete build spec is available, at what looks like a solid deal for $1900 including the 40mm travel Suntour GVX gravel suspension fork, a Microshift Sword 10-speed gravel groupset, and Tranz X 125mm travel dropper seatpost.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://konaworld.com/\" target=\"_blank\">KonaWorld.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/kona-ouroboros-adds-aluminum-frame-expanding-adventure-gravel-bike-family/\">Kona Ouroboros Adds Aluminum Frame, Expanding Adventure Gravel Bike Family</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"17e9fe7c59814bb77ec33b16202e5d6157ec9144c979364508bdd3e7078c561f","category":"Cycling"}